                            <comment id="14656370" author="JIRAUSER20205" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2024 15:55:17 -0700"  >There are two tests without cleaning up socket files.&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/java/nio/channels/unixdomain/Bind.java&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/java/nio/channels/unixdomain/NonBlockingAccept.java</comment>
                            <comment id="14656355" author="JIRAUSER20205" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2024 14:11:33 -0700"  >Some tests create temp files in the default java.io.tmpdir directory without cleaning up those files.&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/com/sun/management/HotSpotDiagnosticMXBean/CheckOrigin.java&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/jdk/jfr/api/consumer/filestream/TestOrdered.java&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/jdk/jfr/api/consumer/filestream/TestReuse.java&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/jdk/jfr/threading/TestManyVirtualThreads.java&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/sun/security/pkcs12/P12SecretKey.java&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Some tests delete temp files outside the finally block, which may result in files not being cleaned up upon test failure.&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/java/io/File/CheckPermission.java&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/java/io/FileInputStream/NegativeAvailable.java&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/java/util/zip/ZipFile/ZeroDate.java&lt;br/&gt;
open/test/jdk/jdk/nio/zipfs/ZeroDate.java</comment>
                            <comment id="14655870" author="michaelm" created="Fri, 8 Mar 2024 08:20:18 -0800"  >Some things to check for in test case sources would be direct calls to:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
java.io.File.createTempFile&lt;br/&gt;
java.nio.file.Files.createTempFile&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Also, NIO socket channels (server sockets) created using StandardProtocolFamily.UNIX and which are implicitly bound to a local address (bind called with address param null) end up with their socket file created in the temp directory. The NIO API specifies that these files must be explicitly removed when no longer required. So, there could be some tests using this API but not cleaning up afterwards.</comment>
                            <comment id="14655786" author="michaelm" created="Fri, 8 Mar 2024 02:44:02 -0800"  >Should jtreg set the system property ${java.io.tmpdir} to its own temporary directory unless overridden by the test?</comment>
